Overview
This project aims to build a vehicle due-diligence engine that helps buyers evaluate whether a specific car is a smart purchase before committing money.

The goal is to reduce uncertainty, research time, and financial risk when purchasing used or new vehicles.

This is not a marketplace or listing aggregator.
It is a decision-support system that analyzes a vehicle and generates a structured risk and value report.

Problem Statement
Buying a vehicle requires navigating:

Inconsistent pricing
Hidden recalls
Reliability concerns
High mileage uncertainty
Potential scams
Emotional bias during negotiation
Most buyers manually research forums, recall databases, pricing sites, and reliability reports across multiple sources.

This project consolidates those steps into a single structured analysis.

Core Functionality
User Input
The system will accept:

VIN (optional but recommended)
Year
Make
Model
Trim (optional)
Mileage
Asking price
ZIP code / location
Optional listing text
System Architecture (High-Level)
1. Data Layer (Structured & Factual)
VIN decoding via NHTSA vPIC
Recall data retrieval
Vehicle specifications
Safety data
Stored reliability heuristics
This layer provides verifiable, structured data.

2. Scoring Engine (Deterministic Logic)
The system calculates:

Deal Score (0–100)
Price-to-mileage evaluation
Risk tier classification (Low / Medium / High)
Recall severity weighting
Reliability category
This layer must be rules-based and explainable.
No AI-generated guessing is allowed in scoring logic.

3. AI Reasoning Layer
The AI layer is responsible for:

Explaining score breakdown
Summarizing common issues
Generating inspection checklist
Producing negotiation guidance
Highlighting walk-away conditions
The AI must only reason on provided structured data.
It must not hallucinate facts or invent reliability claims.

Output
The system generates a structured report containing:

Deal Score
Risk Level
Recall Summary
Known Reliability Concerns
What to Inspect
Negotiation Advice
Clear disclaimers
What This Project Is Not
Not a car listing site
